<div class="modal-body">
            
                            <h2 class="profile-name">Meet Ashley!</h2>

                            <p lang="en"><img src="../images/gallery/ashley-thumb.jpg" alt="Ashley" class="img-responsive profilePic" />Ashley is described as a sweet and happy girl. It has been stated that she is a bright, smiley, energetic teen! Ashley enjoys swimming and outdoor activities. She enjoys being social and loves to give hugs, smile and wave at others.  She loves all things girly, but is also fascinated with wheels, including carts, skates, and shopping baskets. Ashley enjoys coloring, drawing, and playing with baby dolls. She likes being in the kitchen and her favorite time of day is lunch. She is not a picky eater and her favorite food is chicken nuggets.</p>

                            <p lang="en">Ashley will be in 11th grade in a self-contained special education classroom. She does have an IEP in place. She does well in school and it is reported that school staff adore her. </p>
                            <p lang="en">Ashley will do well in any family setting. She would love to have siblings and would do well with a single mother, or a two-parent home. She needs a family who is familiar with her special needs, or willing to learn to care for her. She will need to continue her services both at school and in the home. </p>
                            <p lang="en"></p>
                            <p lang="en"></p>
                            <p lang="en"></p>

